      // click lands in a textgrid; edits route to THIS region — translating the
      // caret to its local coords — rather than re-resolving the region from raw
      // (x,y) every keystroke. That coordinate re-resolution is the root of the
      // whole "text jumps into the neighbouring box at the shared edge" class of
      // bugs: typing along a row reaches the box's right edge, which is another
      // box's strict cell, and the keystroke defects there. The caret OWNS its
      // region until the user clicks elsewhere. (View-state; never serialized.)
