      // Multi-caret column edit (§8.3): `caret` is always the PRIMARY (the
      // anchor for blink, movement and view-state serialization). `extraCarets`
      // holds the additional column carets ({x,y} each), empty in the ordinary
      // single-caret editor — when it is empty every edit path is bit-for-bit
      // the v1 behaviour. The set is transient view-state; it is never stored
      // and never serialized into a viewport/tab (only the primary is).
