      kernel.on("input:suggest", function () { open(); });
      // AUTO-OPEN on a provider SIGIL (Thread B): typing "/" pops the create menu — no Ctrl+Space needed.
      // Fires only when the typed char IS some provider's sigil AND, once written, that sigil provider
      // claims the caret's prefix — i.e. a fresh "/" at a token start. A mid-token slash (a URL "http://")
      // is NOT claimed (sigil not at index 0) → no popup. Deferred a tick so the char lands on the plane
